      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The libertarian perspective you're looking for is rooted in the idea of the \"Lockean Bundle of Rights,\" which posits that individuals possess inherent, inalienable rights to their own property, including digital property. This concept, inspired by John Locke, asserts that individuals have a natural right to control and protect their own information, and that the state's authority to regulate digital communication is illegitimate because it encroaches upon this fundamental right.",
